<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2028] ActiveMQSessionExecutor.taskRunner usage is very non-thread-safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2028</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;cmon guys,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                    if (taskRunnerCreated.compareAndSet(false, true)) {&lt;br/&gt;
                        if (taskRunner == null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                            taskRunner = session.connection.getSessionTaskRunner().createTaskRunner(this,
                                    &quot;ActiveMQ Session: &quot; + session.getSessionId());
                        }
&lt;p&gt;                    }&lt;br/&gt;
                    taskRunner.wakeup();&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;is not anywhere close to thread safe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m seeing JmsClientAckTest and JmsRedeliveredTest failing due to this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
